From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000030 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 02:10:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: twl-core: export twl_is_ready(); OMAP4: stop pre-probe
 twl i2c attempts

After 0023 stopped latching a failed SMPS_OFFSET efuse read (so the
real efuse gets picked up once twl-core probes), every twl6030 vsel/uv
conversion issued before the DT-probed twl i2c device binds retried
the read - and each doomed attempt logged "twl: not initialized" from
twl_get_regmap(). The VC+VP channel init for the IVA and CORE domains
(omap_voltage_late_init, a late_initcall at ~0.78 s vs twl probe at
~3.6 s) makes exactly 22 such attempts per boot: per domain 3 nonzero
VC voltages (on/onlp/ret) x2 attempts (uv_to_vsel reads once itself
and once via its vsel_to_uv range check) + the zero off-voltage x1 +
2 VP limits x2 = 11, times two domains. The patch-0014 retask poll
added 2 more by probing readiness with a raw register read.

Fix the ordering instead of the symptom: export a twl_is_ready()
predicate from twl-core (true once all regmaps exist and twl_priv is
ready - the exact condition for usable transfers), gate the efuse read
attempt on it (the steelhead seed still covers pre-probe conversions),
switch the retask poll to the predicate (its twl6030_pm_modify calls
still verify real bus transactions), and latch the real efuse in the
retask work as soon as twl is up. Zero prints, identical behaviour.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
@@ -413,6 +413,20 @@
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(twl_rev);
 
 /**
+ * twl_is_ready - can twl_i2c_read/write actually reach the chip yet?
+ *
+ * Lets early platform code (e.g. the OMAP4 voltage layer, which runs from a
+ * late_initcall long before the DT-probed twl i2c device binds) check for
+ * readiness instead of issuing doomed transfers that each log
+ * "twl: not initialized".
+ */
+bool twl_is_ready(void)
+{
+	return twl_priv && twl_priv->ready;
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(twl_is_ready);
+
+/**
  * twl_get_regmap - Get the regmap associated with the given module
  * @mod_no: module number
  *
--- a/include/linux/mfd/twl.h
+++ b/include/linux/mfd/twl.h
@@ -152,6 +152,7 @@
 #define TWL4030_CLASS_ID 		0x4030
 #define TWL6030_CLASS_ID 		0x6030
 unsigned int twl_rev(void);
+bool twl_is_ready(void);
 #define GET_TWL_REV (twl_rev())
 #define TWL_CLASS_IS(class, id)			\
 static inline int twl_class_is_ ##class(void)	\
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_twl.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap_twl.c
@@ -61,7 +61,15 @@
 	if (is_offset_valid)
 		return;
 
-	if (!twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &smps_offset,
+	/*
+	 * Don't even attempt the i2c read until twl-core is ready: the
+	 * conversions below run from omap_voltage_late_init() well before the
+	 * DT-probed twl i2c device binds, and with the no-latch-on-failure
+	 * behaviour every doomed attempt logged "twl: not initialized" - a
+	 * x22 burst per boot (VC+VP channel init for IVA and CORE).
+	 */
+	if (twl_is_ready() &&
+	    !twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &smps_offset,
 			     REG_SMPS_OFFSET)) {
 		is_offset_valid = true;
 		return;
@@ -443,10 +451,12 @@
 static void omap4460_vdd_mpu_retask_work(struct work_struct *work)
 {
 	static int attempts;
-	u8 tmp;
 
-	/* TWL6030 control i2c (slave 0x48) initialized yet? */
-	if (twl_i2c_read_u8(TWL6030_MODULE_ID0, &tmp, 0x00)) {
+	/* TWL6030 control i2c (slave 0x48) initialized yet? Ask twl-core
+	 * instead of probing with a read - each failed probe read logged
+	 * "twl: not initialized". The retask's own twl6030_pm_modify calls
+	 * still verify real bus transactions and abort on error. */
+	if (!twl_is_ready()) {
 		if (++attempts < 60) {
 			schedule_delayed_work(to_delayed_work(work),
 					      msecs_to_jiffies(500));
@@ -457,6 +467,10 @@
 		return;
 	}
 
+	/* twl is up: latch the real SMPS_OFFSET efuse (replaces the boot-time
+	 * steelhead seed; idempotent once valid). */
+	twl6030_read_smps_offset();
+
 	omap4460_vdd_mpu_do_retask();
 }
 static DECLARE_DELAYED_WORK(omap4460_mpu_retask_dwork,
